<p><b>Arbitrary 
detention;  
Freedom of 
expression;  
Freedom of 
peaceful assembly 
and of association;  
Human rights 
defenders;   
</b> 
</p>
<p>Allegations of sentencing of eight student protestors to prison terms following their 
participation in peaceful demonstrations in the Tibet Autonomous Region in 
November 2012. According to the information received, following a peaceful protest 
that called for, inter alia, equality among nationalities, and respect for and freedom to 
study the Tibetan language,  the Gonghe County People&#8217;s Court, on 10 April 2013, 
handed down prison sentences to  the following student protestors from the Tsolho 
Technical School for &#8220;illegally holding demonstration&#8221; and &#8220;causing harm to social 
stability&#8221;: Mr Sangye Bum was sentenced to four years in prison; Messrs Kunsang 
Bum, Lhaten and Jampa Tsering were sentenced to three years and six months in 
prison; Messrs Wangyal Tsering and Choekyong Kyap were sentenced to three years 
and three months in prison; and Messrs Tsering Tashi and Dola were sentenced to 
three years in prison.  
</p>
<p>12/07/2013 
 
