<p><b>Disappearances;  
Freedom of 
peaceful assembly 
and of association;  
Torture;   
</b></p>
<p>Alleged enforced disappearance and risk of torture of Mr Nazrul Islam, an opposition 
party member. According to the information received, during the night of 11 April 
2013, Mr Nazrul Islam, the Joypurhat District Secretary of Jamaat-e-Islami, a political 
party belonging to a multi-party opposition alliance, was allegedly abducted from his 
home in Saheb Parha, Joypurhat District. It is reported that the alleged perpetrators 
identified themselves as being &#8220;from the administration&#8221; and took Mr Islam on a 
minibus to an unknown location. At the time of transmission of this communication, 
the fate and whereabouts of Mr Islam remained unknown. 
