November 2012. According to the information received, Mr Wangchuk Dorje, a 
student of the Middle School of Nationalities, was recently sentenced to four years&#8217; 
imprisonment as one of the main organizers of peaceful student demonstrations which 
took place on 9 November 2012 in Tongren county, Huangnan Tibetan Autonomous 
Prefecture. The peaceful protestors demanded, inter alia, freedom to study the Tibetan 
language, equality between nationalities, and the return of the Dalai Lama. A number 
of students were physically assaulted by law enforcement authorities, and some had to 
be treated in hospitals for injuries. 
