<p>Alleged killing of a Baha&#8217;i. According to the information received, on 24 August 
2013, Mr Ataollah Rezvani, a member of the Baha&#8217;i religious minority in the Islamic 
Republic of Iran, was shot in the back of the head by an unknown person. His body 
was reportedly found in his car, near the railway station on the outskirts of the city of 
Bandar Abbas. It is alleged that Mr Rezvani may have been killed because of his 
religion. Reportedly, he had received threats and been intimidated previously on the 
basis of his religious belief. 
