<p>LAO 1/2013 
<b>R&#233;publique 
D&#233;mocratique 
Populaire Lao 
</b> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p><b>Freedom of 
peaceful assembly 
and of association;  
Human rights 
defenders;   
</b></p>
<p>Alleged violation of the right to freedom of association. According to the information 
received, the draft Guidelines for the implementation of the Prime Minister&#8217;s Decree 
on International Non-Governmental Organisations, contains several provisions that, if 
adopted without further changes, may seriously compromise the enjoyment of the 
right to freedom of association in the Lao People&#8217;s Democratic Republic. 
</p>
<p>06/12/2013 
 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>14/10/2013 
AL 
 
</p>
<p>MDV 3/2013 
<b>Maldives 
</b> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p><b>Freedom of 
expression;   
</b> 
</p>
<p>Alleged arson attack on a TV channel. According to the information received, on 7 
October 2013, around 4.45 a.m., the studio of the Raajje TV was set on fire by at least 
six heavily armed gunmen. Consequently, all broadcast equipment, transmission and 
computer systems were destroyed. The Raajje TV channel is known to be one of the 
most popular TV stations in the Maldives, and this arson attack is reportedly seen as 
an attempt to silence its broadcast services. 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
