<p>EGY 15/2013 
<b>Egypt 
</b> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p><b>Arbitrary 
detention;  
Torture;   
</b> 
</p>
<p>Alleged arbitrary detention, torture and denial of medical treatment. According to the 
information received, in August 2013, Mr Ahmed Hassan Al-Din was reportedly 
arrested by law enforcement and State security officers and taken to Tajamo Awawal 
Police Station in New Cairo District 2. While detained, Mr Al-Din was allegedly 
beaten and insulted by several police officers. On 20 August, he was transferred to the 
State Security Investigation building, where he was reportedly put in a small cell and 
left handcuffed in a stress position for eight hours. While blindfolded, he was 
reportedly punched several times in the face before being taken to an interrogation 
room. He was later transferred to Tora prison in Aqrab, where he remained detained at 
the time of writing. It is reported that Mr Al-Din suffers from back pain as a result of 
falling twice when forced to walk down the stairs blindfolded. In an attempt to protest 
his situation, on 24 October 2013, Mr Al-Din began a hunger strike and on 4 
November, he refused to take liquids.  
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
