</b></p>
<p>Alleged death threats against a human rights defender broadcast by State media. 
According to the information received, on 4 November 2013 the Sri Lankan 
Broadcasting Corporation broadcast, a radio programme in which serious threats were 
made against the life of Ms Nimalka Fernando. The threats were made after the airing 
of a recording that had been broadcast the day before on Hiru TV with the approval of 
Ms Fernando. It is further reported that the presenters of the radio show endorsed and 
encouraged the threats being made against her. 
