<p>Alleged arbitrary detention and ill-treatment. According to the information received, Mr 
Wickramasinghe Arachchige Ranjith Chandrasiri Perera was arrested by police officers of 
the Criminal Investigation Division (CID) and the Colombo Crime Division on 14 May 
2009 without arrest warrant. He was allegedly severely assaulted while being held at the 
Colombo Crime Division (CCD) in Dematagoda. On 23 June 2009, Mr Wickramasinghe 
was allegedly blindfolded and taken to an unknown location, where he was severely 
beaten. 
