<p>Alleged legislative amendments increasing fines and criminalizing breaches of the 
regulations regarding the organization and participation in peaceful assemblies, which 
may be contrary to the fundamental right to freedom of peaceful assembly. According to 
the information received, on 2 November 2012, the Parliament of Azerbaijan adopted 
new amendments to the law on Freedom of Assembly, the Administrative Offences Code 
and the Criminal Code. Individuals breaching the Freedom of Assembly laws can now 
reportedly be prosecuted criminally or detained under administrative arrest. Also the fines 
for participating in and organizing unlawful gatherings have been increased massively. 
