<p>Alleged forced evictions of thousands of families from the Majombe neighbourhood of 
Cacuaco municipality in Luanda. According to information received, on 1, 2, 4 and 5 
February 2013, thousands of families from the Maiombe neighbourhood of Cacuaco 
municipality, in the capital of Luanda, have been forcibly evicted by Government 
officials and private security forces, and their houses have been demolished. It is further 
alleged that some individuals have been beaten in the process, and that at least six people 
have been arrested when attempting to resist the demolitions. Allegedly, hundreds of 
other families who remained in the ruins of their homes after the demolitions are 
currently at risk of being forcibly evicted. 
