information received, on the morning of 23 February 2013 a demolition squad from the 
Lagos State Government began demolishing houses in the Oke-Ilu-Eri area of Badia East 
in Lagos. As many as 30 houses are reported to have been demolished within the hour 
and thousands more residents are to be further evicted and their houses demolished. 
Reportedly, no appropriate prior notice of the evictions and demolitions was provided to 
the residents. 
