</b> 
</p>
<p>Alleged harassment and threats against a Buddhist activist, writer and human rights 
defender. According to the information received, in June and July 2012, Mr Le Cong 
Cau was prohibited from joining demonstrations during the massive crackdown on anti-
China protesters around the country. Following an intensive 7-hour interrogation with 
regard to the articles he wrote online about the Communist Party&#8217;s policies on Buddhism 
and China, he was reportedly not allowed to leave his house which was surrounded by 
police. In March 2013, he was again summoned for another interrogation, which lasted 
for two and a half days. Security Police accused him of slandering the regime and 
spreading propaganda and, before releasing him, forced him to write a statement 
admitting that he had written articles criticizing the Communist Party.     
</p>
<p>02/07/2013 
 
