<p>Alleged practices of solitary confinement and inhuman or degrading conditions in 
detention. According to the information received, between 400 and 500 inmates at the 
United States Penitentiary Administrative Maximum Facility (&#8220;ADX&#8221;) in Florence, 
Colorado, are held in prolonged solitary confinement, sometimes for several years, and 
are denied adequate medical treatment. It is alleged that these practices cause severe 
physical and mental pain and suffering rising to the level of torture and other cruel, 
inhuman or degrading treatment. 
